1
00:00:11,800 --> 00:00:15,280
[1997]

2
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:21,920
Hurry up!

3
00:00:22,030 --> 00:00:23,190
Are you hidden?

4
00:00:23,440 --> 00:00:24,500
Just wait a minute!

5
00:00:27,070 --> 00:00:28,440
What are you doing?

6
00:00:32,350 --> 00:00:33,000
Doing...

7
00:00:33,290 --> 00:00:34,220
Doing homework.

8
00:00:34,330 --> 00:00:35,720
Then can I hide at your house?

9
00:00:35,720 --> 00:00:36,600
Y-Yes.

10
00:00:36,960 --> 00:00:37,670
Really?

11
00:00:39,590 --> 00:00:40,850
You can hide in my room.

12
00:00:44,390 --> 00:00:45,720
I'll take you upstairs.

13
00:01:00,740 --> 00:01:01,180
No,

14
00:01:01,360 --> 00:01:02,960
that spot is too easy to find.

15
00:01:10,380 --> 00:01:11,460
Can I hide there?

16
00:01:12,039 --> 00:01:12,640
Yes.

17
00:01:22,340 --> 00:01:23,030
Hold on!

18
00:01:23,430 --> 00:01:24,480
Don't betray me.

19
00:01:24,720 --> 00:01:25,890
Don't tell anyone!

20
00:01:26,630 --> 00:01:27,320
I won't.

21
00:01:37,009 --> 00:01:39,270
They definitely won't find me this time.

22
00:01:41,580 --> 00:01:44,300
This seems a bit boring.

23
00:01:54,720 --> 00:01:56,190
I'm asking you what you're doing!

24
00:01:56,190 --> 00:01:58,050
Why aren't you saying something?

25
00:01:58,110 --> 00:01:59,539
Always hiding things, sneaking around!

26
00:01:59,539 --> 00:02:00,750
What are you up to?

27
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:03,560
Say something!

28
00:02:03,890 --> 00:02:05,360
Always wearing that cold expression—

29
00:02:05,360 --> 00:02:07,220
you don't look like a child at all!

30
00:02:09,280 --> 00:02:10,340
What are you doing?

31
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:13,030
Waiting for your dad to come back
so you can tell on me?

32
00:02:13,030 --> 00:02:13,990
Let me tell you—

33
00:02:14,740 --> 00:02:16,860
your dad doesn't have time
to come back at all!

34
00:02:16,860 --> 00:02:19,190
I cook and wash clothes for you every day!

35
00:02:19,300 --> 00:02:20,340
I take care of you!

36
00:02:20,370 --> 00:02:21,020
And you?

37
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:23,490
Have you ever even smiled at me?

38
00:02:23,900 --> 00:02:25,100
You still dare to run?

39
00:02:25,210 --> 00:02:26,210
Stop right there!

40
00:02:27,020 --> 00:02:28,110
You little brat!

41
00:02:28,410 --> 00:02:29,530
Say something!

42
00:02:30,530 --> 00:02:31,480
Run!

43
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:33,550
You two!

44
00:02:34,260 --> 00:02:35,390
Stop right there!

45
00:04:06,830 --> 00:04:12,750
[Sunsets Secrets Regrets]

46
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:15,390
[Episode 7]

47
00:04:51,430 --> 00:04:52,270
Jin!

48
00:04:53,920 --> 00:04:55,390
Jin, are you home?

49
00:04:58,520 --> 00:04:59,159
Zhou Jin.

50
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:01,480
Jin, get up!

51
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:02,680
Jin!

52
00:05:05,390 --> 00:05:06,310
Jin!

53
00:05:07,470 --> 00:05:08,550
Jin!

54
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:11,180
-Get up, Jin!
-Zhou Jin.

55
00:05:12,530 --> 00:05:13,530
Help me turn over.

56
00:05:13,760 --> 00:05:14,150
Jin!

57
00:05:14,180 --> 00:05:14,980
My arm is numb.

58
00:05:15,270 --> 00:05:16,000
Sorry, sorry.

59
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:16,750
Jin, get up!

60
00:05:16,750 --> 00:05:17,480
I'll do it myself.

61
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:18,850
Time to get up and pee!

62
00:05:19,070 --> 00:05:20,870
Sorry, I slept too deeply last night.

63
00:05:20,870 --> 00:05:21,330
Jin!

64
00:05:21,350 --> 00:05:22,050
Are you okay?

65
00:05:22,050 --> 00:05:22,570
I'm fine.

66
00:05:22,570 --> 00:05:24,480
Jin, Jin!

67
00:05:24,950 --> 00:05:26,240
I'll go see what he wants.

68
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:26,920
Get up!

69
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:29,110
You stretch first.

70
00:05:29,540 --> 00:05:30,460
Jin!

71
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:36,720
Jin! Jin!

72
00:05:36,830 --> 00:05:38,070
What are you doing?

73
00:05:38,070 --> 00:05:40,040
Stop yelling, Bin!

74
00:05:41,430 --> 00:05:42,630
You're waking me up!

75
00:05:42,630 --> 00:05:44,830
What's going on so early in the morning?

76
00:05:45,510 --> 00:05:46,970
Where's that guy of yours?

77
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:48,480
What guy?

78
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:50,680
Jin.

79
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,240
Look at you, getting all grown up.

80
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:54,190
You've got a boyfriend,

81
00:05:54,190 --> 00:05:55,990
and you didn't even tell us, huh?

82
00:05:57,159 --> 00:05:58,510
He's not my boyfriend.

83
00:05:58,560 --> 00:06:00,040
Oh, cut the act.

84
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:02,560
I heard everything clearly last night.

85
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:04,070
M-Mom.

86
00:06:04,390 --> 00:06:06,070
My God, that was so disgusting!

87
00:06:06,070 --> 00:06:07,270
Watch your mouth.

88
00:06:08,830 --> 00:06:09,600
What, are you mad?

89
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,480
So now we can't even talk about it?

90
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:11,630
I told you—

91
00:06:11,630 --> 00:06:12,890
he's not my boyfriend.

92
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:15,950
I'm married.

93
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:20,990
You came fully prepared, huh?

94
00:06:20,990 --> 00:06:22,160
You're messing with me, eh?

95
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:23,160
I'm not.

96
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:25,870
Really not messing with me?

97
00:06:25,870 --> 00:06:27,070
Really not.

98
00:06:27,870 --> 00:06:28,800
You're serious?

99
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:31,160
I'm serious.

100
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:33,210
I'm really married.

101
00:06:34,190 --> 00:06:35,630
Wait, wait, wait...

102
00:06:35,630 --> 00:06:36,560
Why did you do it?

103
00:06:36,750 --> 00:06:38,270
What do you think you're doing?

104
00:06:38,270 --> 00:06:39,630
What about Jiang Cheng, then?

105
00:06:39,630 --> 00:06:40,790
You've liked him for so many years,

106
00:06:40,790 --> 00:06:41,800
and now you just get married like that?

107
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:43,000
What the hell is that?

108
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:45,159
Bin,

109
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:47,950
I know I was wrong
not to tell you about my marriage.

110
00:06:47,950 --> 00:06:48,920
But can you please stop

111
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:51,050
mentioning Jiang Cheng in front of me?

112
00:06:51,390 --> 00:06:51,830
No.

113
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:52,360
No.

114
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:53,720
Why?

115
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:54,560
Why can't I mention him?

116
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:55,390
What makes it off-limits?

117
00:06:55,390 --> 00:06:56,870
Because I want to move on.

118
00:07:05,810 --> 00:07:06,610
What...

119
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,630
Whatever happened
between you and Jiang Cheng,

120
00:07:08,630 --> 00:07:09,690
I don't want to ask.

121
00:07:10,030 --> 00:07:11,690
And I don't want to take sides.

122
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:12,680
Yes.

123
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:14,480
I know

124
00:07:15,390 --> 00:07:16,950
people change when they grow up.

125
00:07:16,950 --> 00:07:18,240
But some things can't change,

126
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:19,560
and they won't change!

127
00:07:20,830 --> 00:07:21,680
Jin,

128
00:07:22,310 --> 00:07:24,040
actually, you don't know this.

129
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:26,270
But before you had feelings
for Jiang Cheng,

130
00:07:26,270 --> 00:07:27,680
Jiang Cheng told me

131
00:07:27,840 --> 00:07:28,870
that he felt...

132
00:07:31,950 --> 00:07:32,630
Bin!

133
00:07:33,690 --> 00:07:35,870
You're here early in the morning!
What's up?

134
00:07:35,870 --> 00:07:36,750
Uh, Uncle!

135
00:07:37,480 --> 00:07:39,430
My mom told me to bring you a duck.

136
00:07:39,850 --> 00:07:41,390
You can stew it for soup tonight.

137
00:07:41,390 --> 00:07:41,870
Okay, okay.

138
00:07:41,870 --> 00:07:42,870
For tonight's soup,

139
00:07:42,870 --> 00:07:44,860
and you brought it here
so early in the morning?

140
00:07:44,860 --> 00:07:46,320
I-I-I was just passing by.

141
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:48,560
D-Don't go yet!

142
00:07:48,870 --> 00:07:50,720
The pickled cucumbers I made are ready.

143
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:51,630
Take them back with you.

144
00:07:51,630 --> 00:07:53,290
Tell your mom
to keep them in a cool place.

145
00:07:53,290 --> 00:07:53,960
No need, Auntie!

146
00:07:53,960 --> 00:07:55,310
It's not convenient since I'm riding.

147
00:07:55,310 --> 00:07:56,310
Maybe some other time.

148
00:07:56,310 --> 00:07:58,110
Then come over for soup tonight.

149
00:07:58,750 --> 00:07:59,320
No thanks.

150
00:07:59,320 --> 00:07:59,880
What?

151
00:08:00,630 --> 00:08:01,830
Are you guys going out

152
00:08:01,830 --> 00:08:02,600
to eat?

153
00:08:03,310 --> 00:08:03,720
Yes.

154
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:04,560
My...

155
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:06,360
hot pot restaurant just opened.

156
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:07,750
Jin,

157
00:08:08,190 --> 00:08:10,560
how about... we hang out tonight?

158
00:08:11,630 --> 00:08:12,120
Go on!

159
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:13,310
His restaurant is quite good!

160
00:08:13,310 --> 00:08:14,310
I've eaten there!

161
00:08:14,510 --> 00:08:15,520
The flavor's great,

162
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:16,720
and the chef is great!

163
00:08:17,630 --> 00:08:18,310
Alright then.

164
00:08:18,310 --> 00:08:20,510
We'll go prepare lunch.

165
00:08:20,510 --> 00:08:21,770
Time to prepare lunch.

166
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:25,680
Come on.

167
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:27,920
Wei is back too. We can all get together.

168
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:28,680
Wei is back?

169
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:30,510
How long is he staying?

170
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:31,870
Just until the 17th.

171
00:08:32,470 --> 00:08:33,520
His wife is about to give birth.

172
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:35,980
He came back
to take his parents to Jingzhou.

173
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:36,600
Okay.

174
00:08:37,669 --> 00:08:38,360
Hansheng,

175
00:08:38,510 --> 00:08:40,390
let's have hot pot tonight.

176
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,450
I'm fine with anything.

177
00:08:44,150 --> 00:08:44,870
Okay then.

178
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:47,430
Order a half-and-half pot tonight for me.

179
00:08:47,430 --> 00:08:48,960
He can't handle spicy food.

180
00:08:59,910 --> 00:09:00,840
See you tonight!

181
00:09:05,100 --> 00:09:05,900
I'm so pissed.

182
00:09:25,210 --> 00:09:26,740
Do you know how to overtake?

183
00:09:27,270 --> 00:09:28,080
Yeah, Cheng.

184
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:29,420
Switch lanes then.

185
00:09:29,880 --> 00:09:30,450
Okay.

186
00:09:43,030 --> 00:09:43,890
[Jin is married, you know?
She even brought that man home!]

187
00:09:43,890 --> 00:09:44,760
[Seeing her parents smile like that
made me want to cry!]

188
00:09:44,780 --> 00:09:45,570
[Cheng! Say something!
I'm having dinner with them tonight!]

189
00:09:45,570 --> 00:09:46,370
[What do you think about this? Tell me!]

190
00:09:59,150 --> 00:09:59,870
Get out.

191
00:10:00,090 --> 00:10:01,150
What's wrong, Cheng?

192
00:10:01,150 --> 00:10:01,670
Get out!

193
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:47,730
Jiang Cheng?

194
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:50,000
Care to join me for a meal?

195
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,700
Is this how your boss
invites people to eat?

196
00:10:52,700 --> 00:10:53,890
It has nothing to do with Boss He.

197
00:10:53,890 --> 00:10:55,000
I'm the one inviting you.

198
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:55,600
No thanks.

199
00:10:55,610 --> 00:10:56,490
Move your car.

200
00:10:56,520 --> 00:10:57,720
I've got things to do.

201
00:10:59,380 --> 00:11:01,020
If you refuse,

202
00:11:01,050 --> 00:11:02,650
I'll tell the traffic police

203
00:11:02,670 --> 00:11:04,440
that there's something wrong
with your car.

204
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:07,040
You think I'd use my own car
to transport goods?

205
00:11:07,240 --> 00:11:08,240
No, you wouldn't.

206
00:11:09,590 --> 00:11:12,550
But that old silver Buick behind us...

207
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:14,360
Even though I can't see what's inside,

208
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:15,200
I believe

209
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:17,000
they're watching us right now.

210
00:11:18,870 --> 00:11:21,400
I just want to keep you here
for one more night.

211
00:11:24,670 --> 00:11:26,730
The traffic cops are coming this way.

212
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:27,870
Nine.

213
00:11:28,550 --> 00:11:29,240
Eight.

214
00:11:29,790 --> 00:11:30,480
Seven.

215
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:31,870
Six.

216
00:11:32,470 --> 00:11:33,150
Five.

217
00:11:33,720 --> 00:11:34,480
Four.

218
00:11:34,910 --> 00:11:35,600
Three.

219
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:37,000
Two.

220
00:11:37,550 --> 00:11:38,030
One.

221
00:11:39,550 --> 00:11:40,240
You two,

222
00:11:40,360 --> 00:11:41,560
what's going on here?

223
00:11:44,010 --> 00:11:45,310
We'll handle this between ourselves.

224
00:11:45,310 --> 00:11:46,110
I'm in a hurry.

225
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:47,200
And you?

226
00:11:48,030 --> 00:11:48,960
I'm okay with that.

227
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:49,790
With a girl this pretty,

228
00:11:49,790 --> 00:11:50,410
how could I object?

229
00:11:50,410 --> 00:11:51,520
Then take photos

230
00:11:51,870 --> 00:11:52,870
and handle things up front.

231
00:11:52,870 --> 00:11:53,630
The traffic is all jammed behind you.

232
00:11:53,630 --> 00:11:54,480
-Okay.
-Sure!

233
00:12:03,480 --> 00:12:04,750
Mr. Yan, everything is ready.

234
00:12:04,750 --> 00:12:05,960
One guest is already in the private room.

235
00:12:05,960 --> 00:12:06,680
Okay, okay.

236
00:12:06,710 --> 00:12:07,240
What would you like to eat?

237
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:07,840
Tofu skin.

238
00:12:07,910 --> 00:12:08,510
Tofu skin.

239
00:12:09,390 --> 00:12:09,750
Beef.

240
00:12:12,150 --> 00:12:12,960
Wei!

241
00:12:17,630 --> 00:12:18,320
Wei!

242
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:21,790
Not bad, Bin.

243
00:12:22,150 --> 00:12:23,480
You look pretty decent!

244
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:24,360
You bet!

245
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:25,840
Wei!

246
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:26,960
Jin,

247
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:29,530
why don't you make a formal introduction?

248
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:30,480
This is Jiang Hansheng,

249
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:32,240
a professor at Haizhou University
of Political Science and Law.

250
00:12:32,240 --> 00:12:32,740
Nice to meet you.

251
00:12:32,740 --> 00:12:34,090
[Zhan Wei, Section Chief,
Information Department,]

252
00:12:33,150 --> 00:12:33,860
I'm Zhan Wei.

253
00:12:33,860 --> 00:12:34,360
Nice to meet you.

254
00:12:34,090 --> 00:12:35,450
[Binjiang
Provincial Public Security Bureau]

255
00:12:34,510 --> 00:12:36,720
Wei works in the Information Department
at the Provincial Bureau.

256
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:38,270
Haven't you met him before?

257
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:42,000
Professor Jiang, you're quite familiar
with the Provincial Bureau?

258
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,030
I haven't been there in a long time.

259
00:12:43,030 --> 00:12:45,490
I was also
just transferred there recently.

260
00:12:46,030 --> 00:12:46,870
Come on, sit.

261
00:12:46,970 --> 00:12:48,120
Let's sit down and chat.

262
00:12:48,120 --> 00:12:49,080
You guys are making it look like

263
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:50,200
a government work symposium.

264
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:51,080
Quick, sit.

265
00:12:51,080 --> 00:12:52,810
Right. Let's have a seat first.

266
00:12:53,120 --> 00:12:53,670
Wei.

267
00:12:54,930 --> 00:12:56,250
Look at how you're dressed—

268
00:12:56,250 --> 00:12:57,220
like some senior government official.

269
00:12:57,220 --> 00:12:58,730
Don't you know I'm intimidated?

270
00:12:58,730 --> 00:13:00,060
You're always so fussy.

271
00:13:00,370 --> 00:13:01,900
Wei, I knew you'd wear that.

272
00:13:02,630 --> 00:13:03,480
I'm used to it.

273
00:13:04,090 --> 00:13:04,660
Jin,

274
00:13:04,690 --> 00:13:05,750
how are your parents doing?

275
00:13:05,750 --> 00:13:06,410
Are they well?

276
00:13:06,410 --> 00:13:07,210
They're fine.

277
00:13:07,420 --> 00:13:09,410
I haven't seen them in a long time either.

278
00:13:09,410 --> 00:13:09,910
How about this?

279
00:13:09,910 --> 00:13:11,260
It's rare for me to come back.

280
00:13:11,260 --> 00:13:12,390
Tomorrow, I'll go to

281
00:13:12,430 --> 00:13:13,720
your home and visit them.

282
00:13:13,720 --> 00:13:14,270
Okay.

283
00:13:16,550 --> 00:13:17,410
Is this better?

284
00:13:18,350 --> 00:13:19,480
That's more like it!

285
00:13:19,870 --> 00:13:21,400
When you're here with me...

286
00:13:22,270 --> 00:13:23,270
don't put on airs.

287
00:13:29,010 --> 00:13:29,600
Mr. Yan,

288
00:13:29,620 --> 00:13:31,150
most of the signature dishes
have been served.

289
00:13:31,150 --> 00:13:31,840
Here are the dipping sauces.

290
00:13:31,840 --> 00:13:33,240
Is there anything else you need?

291
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:34,400
Well, looking good, right?

292
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:35,550
Bring us some beer.

293
00:13:36,170 --> 00:13:36,770
Two cases.

294
00:13:37,320 --> 00:13:38,820
Two cases? Who can drink all that?

295
00:13:38,820 --> 00:13:39,840
Two pitchers should be enough.

296
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:40,840
He doesn't drink.

297
00:13:41,550 --> 00:13:43,350
Does he not drink alcohol at all,

298
00:13:43,390 --> 00:13:44,790
or just not drink with us?

299
00:13:45,540 --> 00:13:46,800
I'll be driving later.

300
00:13:48,900 --> 00:13:49,470
Okay.

301
00:13:49,690 --> 00:13:51,290
Then, Jin, you drink with us.

302
00:13:51,780 --> 00:13:53,590
How about some baijiu?

303
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:54,910
Beer is fine.

304
00:13:56,270 --> 00:13:57,000
Alright then.

305
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:57,820
Three pitchers of beer.

306
00:13:57,820 --> 00:13:58,750
Coming right up.

307
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:09,000
The utensils are sterilized
at high temperatures.

308
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:10,530
Don't worry. Just use them!

309
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:15,360
What do you think, Jin?

310
00:14:15,360 --> 00:14:17,090
My restaurant is not bad, huh?

311
00:14:17,390 --> 00:14:18,390
It's pretty good.

312
00:14:18,510 --> 00:14:20,840
Finally seeing you do something proper.

313
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:22,200
Fine.

314
00:14:22,680 --> 00:14:23,440
Now,

315
00:14:24,150 --> 00:14:25,680
she's the one lecturing me.

316
00:14:25,890 --> 00:14:26,840
Back in the day,

317
00:14:26,870 --> 00:14:28,530
I thought we were comrades in arms—

318
00:14:28,530 --> 00:14:30,400
fellow C-students, sticking together.

319
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:31,600
Who would've known?

320
00:14:32,430 --> 00:14:33,960
You just up and abandoned me

321
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:35,340
to take the entrance exam for—

322
00:14:35,340 --> 00:14:35,960
what was it—

323
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:37,200
Jingzhou Police Academy.

324
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:39,230
Who wanted to be a C-student with you?

325
00:14:39,230 --> 00:14:40,600
When I went to cram school,

326
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:42,260
didn't I ask you to come along?

327
00:14:42,390 --> 00:14:43,750
You were the one who didn't want to go.

328
00:14:43,750 --> 00:14:45,150
You had to go chasing after
some girl instead.

329
00:14:45,150 --> 00:14:46,610
And now you're blaming me?

330
00:14:47,260 --> 00:14:48,510
Hansheng, you know what?

331
00:14:48,510 --> 00:14:49,600
He was so bad back then,

332
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:51,000
always teaching me how to lie.

333
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:52,670
He told his family he was at cram school,

334
00:14:52,670 --> 00:14:53,760
but actually,

335
00:14:53,820 --> 00:14:55,640
he was out playing with some girl.

336
00:14:55,640 --> 00:14:56,520
Right, Wei?

337
00:14:56,630 --> 00:14:57,320
I remember!

338
00:14:57,440 --> 00:14:58,760
I even covered for him.

339
00:14:59,560 --> 00:15:00,980
See? Wei was always tight-lipped.

340
00:15:00,980 --> 00:15:02,270
He's much more reliable than you.

341
00:15:02,270 --> 00:15:03,470
How am I not reliable?

342
00:15:03,910 --> 00:15:05,510
Didn't I take enough blame for you?

343
00:15:05,510 --> 00:15:07,760
How many times did my parents
beat me because of you?

344
00:15:07,760 --> 00:15:08,830
Come on.

345
00:15:09,950 --> 00:15:12,520
Back then, Chuan protected you,

346
00:15:12,550 --> 00:15:13,930
and Cheng covered for you.

347
00:15:13,930 --> 00:15:15,930
When did your dad ever beat you?

348
00:15:16,480 --> 00:15:18,030
Alright. That was years ago.

349
00:15:18,030 --> 00:15:19,270
You're still holding onto it?

350
00:15:19,270 --> 00:15:20,840
Alright, let's eat. It's boiling.

351
00:15:20,840 --> 00:15:21,970
I remember all of it.

352
00:15:22,710 --> 00:15:24,510
That year, my mom grabbed a broom

353
00:15:24,640 --> 00:15:26,300
and chased me
from one end of the street to the other.

354
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:27,410
My head was already big—

355
00:15:27,410 --> 00:15:28,930
the next day it was even bigger.

356
00:15:28,930 --> 00:15:30,020
My first love

357
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:31,500
dumped me right after that.

358
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:32,830
My poor little heart...

359
00:15:33,030 --> 00:15:34,490
Don't even get me started.

360
00:15:35,230 --> 00:15:36,180
It was all her fault.

361
00:15:36,180 --> 00:15:37,040
She let it slip.

362
00:15:37,050 --> 00:15:38,320
What first love?

363
00:15:38,320 --> 00:15:40,320
Weren't they all your "first love"?

364
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:41,150
Yes.

365
00:15:42,920 --> 00:15:44,380
When it comes to devotion,

366
00:15:44,490 --> 00:15:47,290
I definitely can't
compare to you and Jiang Cheng.

367
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:56,020
Hurry, call a waitress to clean it up.

368
00:15:58,740 --> 00:16:00,000
I'll go get a waitress.

369
00:16:13,450 --> 00:16:14,240
Cheng,

370
00:16:14,650 --> 00:16:17,110
I-I'm having a meal
with Jin and her husband.

371
00:16:17,490 --> 00:16:18,570
Man, this meal...

372
00:16:18,920 --> 00:16:20,040
I feel so choked up.

373
00:16:20,110 --> 00:16:21,640
Why do I feel so suffocated?

374
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:25,440
Eat more.

375
00:16:28,510 --> 00:16:30,170
Mr. Jiang, your guest is here.

376
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:34,080
Mr. Jiang.

377
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:35,480
Come on,

378
00:16:35,870 --> 00:16:37,270
have a seat, pretty lady.

379
00:16:37,750 --> 00:16:38,440
Thank you.

380
00:16:42,390 --> 00:16:42,810
How is it?

381
00:16:42,810 --> 00:16:44,600
Not bad, the place I picked, right?

382
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:45,670
Very good.

383
00:16:45,670 --> 00:16:46,800
You have good taste.

384
00:16:49,480 --> 00:16:50,550
Mr. Yan, all cleaned up.

385
00:16:50,550 --> 00:16:51,960
You used to live at No. 23,

386
00:16:51,980 --> 00:16:52,770
didn't you?

387
00:16:53,270 --> 00:16:53,870
Yes.

388
00:16:54,630 --> 00:16:56,690
We moved after I got into high school.

389
00:17:00,030 --> 00:17:01,600
That young master who lived at No. 23.

390
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:02,810
That's what we used to call him.

391
00:17:02,810 --> 00:17:04,550
Yeah, yeah, that's right.

392
00:17:06,310 --> 00:17:07,750
I heard some other nicknames

393
00:17:07,750 --> 00:17:08,510
too.

394
00:17:09,280 --> 00:17:10,319
Like what?

395
00:17:11,589 --> 00:17:13,790
Just nonsense we said when we were kids.

396
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:17,650
Tastes good.

397
00:17:17,770 --> 00:17:19,829
I need to take this call. You guys eat.

398
00:17:20,680 --> 00:17:21,940
Talk less and eat more.

399
00:17:24,329 --> 00:17:25,990
I really like eating gongcai.

400
00:17:26,589 --> 00:17:27,550
I'll put some in.

401
00:17:31,680 --> 00:17:33,540
What university are you at again?

402
00:17:33,550 --> 00:17:34,770
Haizhou University
of Political Science and Law.

403
00:17:34,770 --> 00:17:35,640
Right, yes.

404
00:17:36,590 --> 00:17:38,650
You're a university professor, huh?

405
00:17:38,720 --> 00:17:39,400
Jin,

406
00:17:39,550 --> 00:17:41,400
how did you get so lucky to marry someone

407
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:42,660
way above your league?

408
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:45,530
It wasn't like that.

409
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:46,920
I courted Zhou Jin.

410
00:17:47,560 --> 00:17:48,620
Have more vegetables.

411
00:17:48,620 --> 00:17:50,350
Too much meat is hard to digest.

412
00:17:54,370 --> 00:17:54,960
Okay.

413
00:18:00,210 --> 00:18:01,090
One is enough.

414
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:19,720
Go on.

415
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:23,400
I

416
00:18:23,400 --> 00:18:25,000
can understand how you feel.

417
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:28,310
You finally outlasted Lai Zhengtian,

418
00:18:28,310 --> 00:18:30,440
and it's the perfect time
to show your skills.

419
00:18:30,440 --> 00:18:31,350
Yet, the supply channels

420
00:18:31,350 --> 00:18:32,680
got cut off.

421
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:34,210
Of course, you're anxious.

422
00:18:34,480 --> 00:18:35,340
But, Mr. Jiang,

423
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:39,730
when all is said and done,
it's Old Scorpion's business.

424
00:18:40,310 --> 00:18:41,030
You,

425
00:18:41,160 --> 00:18:41,830
I,

426
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:43,790
and even Boss He—

427
00:18:43,960 --> 00:18:46,310
we're all just pawns in it.

428
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:48,160
We just need to do

429
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:49,830
our own parts.

430
00:18:50,190 --> 00:18:50,920
Understand?

431
00:18:58,350 --> 00:18:59,160
So, you're saying

432
00:18:59,160 --> 00:19:01,200
I fought my way through hell

433
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:01,960
just to end up

434
00:19:01,960 --> 00:19:03,310
playing delivery boy?

435
00:19:04,550 --> 00:19:06,110
That's your business.

436
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,730
Why are you bringing this to me?

437
00:19:10,500 --> 00:19:13,160
Because you're not
just an ordinary messenger.

438
00:19:19,720 --> 00:19:20,960
You can't bring yourself to turn it off.

439
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:21,820
Just answer it.

440
00:19:24,440 --> 00:19:25,370
Excuse me, then.

441
00:19:26,310 --> 00:19:27,200
Can't I listen?

442
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:31,680
Sure.

443
00:19:37,510 --> 00:19:38,200
Cheng!

444
00:19:39,350 --> 00:19:40,210
Having dinner?

445
00:19:41,090 --> 00:19:42,600
Look who I'm with.

446
00:19:46,110 --> 00:19:47,070
You guys are having dinner?

447
00:19:47,070 --> 00:19:48,200
Yeah, Cheng.

448
00:19:48,680 --> 00:19:49,880
It'd be great if you came over.

449
00:19:49,880 --> 00:19:51,080
Then we'd all be here.

450
00:19:51,830 --> 00:19:52,760
Wait, not quite.

451
00:19:53,440 --> 00:19:54,160
One extra.

452
00:19:54,830 --> 00:19:55,510
Bin.

453
00:19:57,680 --> 00:19:59,160
I've met her once before.

454
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:01,680
Last time we met, I forgot to

455
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:03,070
congratulate her on her marriage.

456
00:20:03,070 --> 00:20:04,160
Pass that on for me.

457
00:20:05,050 --> 00:20:05,690
Cheng!

458
00:20:05,920 --> 00:20:06,920
Alright, I gotta go.

459
00:20:06,920 --> 00:20:07,860
I'm having dinner with a beautiful lady.

460
00:20:07,860 --> 00:20:08,770
That's it. Bye.

461
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:29,530
What are you two staring at?

462
00:20:29,530 --> 00:20:30,720
Why aren't you two eating?

463
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:31,330
Jin,

464
00:20:31,830 --> 00:20:34,430
come out for a sec.
I need to tell you something.

465
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:36,030
Jin!

466
00:20:40,810 --> 00:20:41,400
Zhou Jin.

467
00:20:42,410 --> 00:20:44,810
It's about the thing
you asked me last time.

468
00:20:47,270 --> 00:20:48,600
Can we just eat in peace?

469
00:20:52,600 --> 00:20:54,660
Hansheng, I'll step out for a moment.

470
00:20:54,990 --> 00:20:55,870
Ignore him.

471
00:21:05,310 --> 00:21:06,880
Actually, ever since I saw you yesterday,

472
00:21:06,880 --> 00:21:08,410
I've had a question for you.

473
00:21:09,590 --> 00:21:11,450
I think I know what you want to ask.

474
00:21:12,310 --> 00:21:13,400
So,

475
00:21:13,420 --> 00:21:15,820
wasn't being a police officer good enough?

476
00:21:16,070 --> 00:21:18,070
Anything is better than being a cop.

477
00:21:20,350 --> 00:21:21,580
You were really willing

478
00:21:21,580 --> 00:21:23,240
to give up everything you had?

479
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:25,480
I'm the one who was abandoned.

480
00:21:25,480 --> 00:21:26,720
The one

481
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:29,060
who gets abandoned doesn't get a say.

482
00:21:31,640 --> 00:21:33,110
Boss He asked me to stop you this time

483
00:21:33,110 --> 00:21:34,640
because he wanted me to ask—

484
00:21:34,680 --> 00:21:35,590
is there any way

485
00:21:35,590 --> 00:21:36,730
for us

486
00:21:36,750 --> 00:21:38,550
to regain Old Scorpion's trust?

487
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:41,600
Do you know Old Scorpion?

488
00:21:42,110 --> 00:21:42,830
No.

489
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:44,680
He never shows himself.

490
00:21:44,680 --> 00:21:46,210
He's practically a legend.

491
00:21:47,350 --> 00:21:48,950
It couldn't be you, could it?

492
00:21:53,810 --> 00:21:54,950
Come on, just tell me.

493
00:21:54,950 --> 00:21:56,410
Don't keep me in suspense.

494
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:01,130
In Old Scorpion's dictionary,

495
00:22:01,590 --> 00:22:03,390
the word "trust" doesn't exist.

496
00:22:03,440 --> 00:22:04,720
If that's the case,

497
00:22:04,790 --> 00:22:06,650
we're completely finished then.

498
00:22:07,310 --> 00:22:09,880
I... wouldn't say that.

499
00:22:11,060 --> 00:22:12,060
Old Scorpion...

500
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:14,030
likes surprises.

501
00:22:14,270 --> 00:22:15,200
Surprises?

502
00:22:16,160 --> 00:22:17,000
A tribute,

503
00:22:17,200 --> 00:22:18,200
a show of loyalty—

504
00:22:18,710 --> 00:22:20,170
call it whatever you like.

505
00:22:20,880 --> 00:22:21,770
Boss He,

506
00:22:21,790 --> 00:22:22,650
Lai Zhengtian—

507
00:22:22,790 --> 00:22:23,920
they're old news.

508
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:25,180
But you're different.

509
00:22:25,680 --> 00:22:26,960
You're fresh.

510
00:22:27,900 --> 00:22:28,920
Can you be more specific—

511
00:22:28,920 --> 00:22:30,380
what exactly does he like?

512
00:22:30,750 --> 00:22:32,510
I can tell you...

513
00:22:33,240 --> 00:22:34,240
what he once lost.

514
00:22:34,590 --> 00:22:35,350
What?

515
00:22:36,790 --> 00:22:37,920
Five years ago,

516
00:22:39,270 --> 00:22:40,710
he lost a young man

517
00:22:40,740 --> 00:22:42,690
who meant a great deal to him.

518
00:22:43,440 --> 00:22:44,110
Who?

519
00:22:45,960 --> 00:22:47,440
That's all I know.

520
00:22:47,550 --> 00:22:48,240
Sorry.

521
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:51,090
I can't help you any more than that.

522
00:22:53,070 --> 00:22:53,750
Cheers.

523
00:23:02,610 --> 00:23:04,270
It's been years since we last met.

524
00:23:04,270 --> 00:23:05,270
And you know what?

525
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:07,260
I still find you just as annoying.

526
00:23:07,770 --> 00:23:09,900
I couldn't stand you when we were kids.

527
00:23:10,510 --> 00:23:12,240
And I still can't stand you now.

528
00:23:12,830 --> 00:23:15,710
You were basically
Zhou Jin's little shadow back then,

529
00:23:15,710 --> 00:23:17,240
always trailing after her.

530
00:23:17,510 --> 00:23:19,640
She never even gave you the time of day.

531
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:20,960
And now?

532
00:23:21,890 --> 00:23:23,350
She actually married you.

533
00:23:25,350 --> 00:23:26,750
Let me ask you something.

534
00:23:27,070 --> 00:23:28,310
Why are you with her?

535
00:23:30,680 --> 00:23:32,140
Is it because you like her?

536
00:23:33,030 --> 00:23:33,680
Or...

537
00:23:35,720 --> 00:23:37,780
because you couldn't accept losing?

538
00:23:38,110 --> 00:23:38,960
However

539
00:23:39,420 --> 00:23:40,350
you see me

540
00:23:40,910 --> 00:23:41,840
doesn't matter.

541
00:23:43,070 --> 00:23:44,470
What about Zhou Jin then?

542
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:47,960
If it weren't for the fact
that her parents are getting old

543
00:23:47,960 --> 00:23:49,490
and she's the only one left,

544
00:23:49,530 --> 00:23:51,660
do you think she would've married you?

545
00:23:52,010 --> 00:23:53,460
You used to live in Zhizi Alley.

546
00:23:53,460 --> 00:23:54,420
You know that.

547
00:23:54,590 --> 00:23:56,570
You know who Zhou Jin

548
00:23:56,590 --> 00:23:59,050
really considered family since childhood.

549
00:24:00,030 --> 00:24:01,590
Sorry, Professor Jiang!

550
00:24:01,590 --> 00:24:03,350
I kept Jin outside for a bit.

551
00:24:03,590 --> 00:24:04,050
Come on.

552
00:24:05,830 --> 00:24:07,030
You're finally back.

553
00:24:07,510 --> 00:24:08,190
Just in time.

554
00:24:08,190 --> 00:24:08,650
Come on.

555
00:24:09,880 --> 00:24:10,880
Professor Jiang,

556
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:13,270
the young master over at No. 23.

557
00:24:14,100 --> 00:24:14,860
I wish you

558
00:24:15,190 --> 00:24:16,750
a long and happy marriage.

559
00:24:17,350 --> 00:24:18,310
Come on, cheers.

560
00:24:18,470 --> 00:24:19,670
I told you,

561
00:24:19,780 --> 00:24:20,780
he doesn't drink.

562
00:24:21,160 --> 00:24:22,090
It's different.

563
00:24:22,200 --> 00:24:22,790
This is

564
00:24:23,270 --> 00:24:24,590
a toast to you.

565
00:24:25,160 --> 00:24:26,060
He must drink it.

566
00:24:26,060 --> 00:24:26,590
Right?

567
00:24:27,550 --> 00:24:28,590
He has to drive today.

568
00:24:28,590 --> 00:24:29,320
-Come on.
-I…

569
00:24:31,950 --> 00:24:32,670
Thank you.

570
00:24:33,080 --> 00:24:33,740
Bottoms up.

571
00:24:36,770 --> 00:24:37,370
Hansheng.

572
00:24:40,560 --> 00:24:41,960
Alright, that's enough.

573
00:24:46,510 --> 00:24:47,440
The beer is weak.

574
00:24:47,840 --> 00:24:48,640
Waitress,

575
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:50,200
bring us some baijiu!

576
00:24:50,210 --> 00:24:51,810
Enough. What are you doing?

577
00:24:52,030 --> 00:24:52,750
No more drinking.

578
00:24:52,750 --> 00:24:53,210
Come on!

579
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:05,460
I'm leaving early tomorrow morning.

580
00:25:06,920 --> 00:25:09,120
You won't drive into me again, will you?

581
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:11,400
Boss He just told us to follow you

582
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:13,160
to see where you delivered the goods

583
00:25:13,160 --> 00:25:14,560
and what the new route is.

584
00:25:16,790 --> 00:25:18,200
So...

585
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:22,360
you're not planning to
follow your boss's orders?

586
00:25:29,630 --> 00:25:30,420
Did some people

587
00:25:30,420 --> 00:25:31,950
follow the delivery truck?

588
00:25:36,900 --> 00:25:37,450
You two,

589
00:25:37,660 --> 00:25:38,860
what's going on here?

590
00:25:39,480 --> 00:25:41,070
We'll handle this between ourselves.

591
00:25:41,070 --> 00:25:41,900
What about you?

592
00:25:41,900 --> 00:25:42,760
I'm okay with that.

593
00:25:42,760 --> 00:25:44,510
With a girl this pretty,
how could I object?

594
00:25:44,510 --> 00:25:45,640
Then take photos

595
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:46,920
and handle things up front.

596
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:47,790
The traffic is all jammed behind you.

597
00:25:47,790 --> 00:25:48,590
-Okay.
-Sure.

598
00:25:48,640 --> 00:25:49,840
Thanks for your help.

599
00:26:00,530 --> 00:26:01,140
Sorry.

600
00:26:01,720 --> 00:26:03,680
Do I need to worry about things
on that end?

601
00:26:03,680 --> 00:26:04,680
We're just tailing you,

602
00:26:04,680 --> 00:26:06,340
not trying to steal the goods.

603
00:26:09,030 --> 00:26:10,090
It doesn't matter.

604
00:26:10,680 --> 00:26:12,280
I'm just a messenger anyway.

605
00:26:19,920 --> 00:26:21,200
Today...

606
00:26:22,680 --> 00:26:23,400
thank you.

607
00:26:24,480 --> 00:26:27,010
Thank you for
being willing to tell me so much.

608
00:26:36,290 --> 00:26:37,490
I'll see you off here.

609
00:26:38,310 --> 00:26:39,240
Get some proper rest.

610
00:26:39,240 --> 00:26:40,370
I'll head off first.

611
00:26:42,350 --> 00:26:43,080
Jiang Cheng!

612
00:26:47,240 --> 00:26:48,970
I don't know what you are doing,

613
00:26:49,250 --> 00:26:50,540
but you're too much of a wild card.

614
00:26:50,540 --> 00:26:51,740
He Wu won't like that.

615
00:26:54,440 --> 00:26:55,550
That's too bad.

616
00:26:55,830 --> 00:26:58,030
I'm still counting on him to make money.

617
00:27:00,580 --> 00:27:02,040
Come up and sit for a while?

618
00:27:11,280 --> 00:27:12,210
I drank too much.

619
00:27:12,310 --> 00:27:13,240
Maybe next time.

620
00:27:27,440 --> 00:27:28,830
Take your pitcher.

621
00:27:30,350 --> 00:27:31,920
We have to finish this one.

622
00:27:32,240 --> 00:27:33,440
That earlier toast

623
00:27:34,200 --> 00:27:35,310
was wishing you'd

624
00:27:35,630 --> 00:27:37,180
have a child soon.

625
00:27:38,100 --> 00:27:39,250
This one

626
00:27:39,640 --> 00:27:41,370
is wishing you a Happy New Year!

627
00:27:41,860 --> 00:27:43,030
Happy New Year, and that's it!

628
00:27:43,030 --> 00:27:43,960
Cheers, come on!

629
00:27:46,800 --> 00:27:47,920
He can drink.

630
00:27:47,940 --> 00:27:49,170
Cheers, come on.

631
00:27:56,360 --> 00:27:57,420
Fill it up, come on.

632
00:28:00,900 --> 00:28:03,050
Stop drinking. Enough! Let's go home.

633
00:28:03,080 --> 00:28:05,400
Don't stop him. He can drink!

634
00:28:05,810 --> 00:28:07,270
You didn't see it earlier.

635
00:28:07,290 --> 00:28:09,490
This guy glared at me when you were out.

636
00:28:09,640 --> 00:28:11,440
He glared at me just now.

637
00:28:12,070 --> 00:28:12,720
Bin,

638
00:28:12,900 --> 00:28:14,070
what exactly are you trying to do today?

639
00:28:14,070 --> 00:28:16,000
What could I do, Jin?

640
00:28:16,230 --> 00:28:18,680
I'm just looking out for you.

641
00:28:18,700 --> 00:28:19,460
Enough.

642
00:28:19,680 --> 00:28:20,310
Jin,

643
00:28:20,480 --> 00:28:21,720
take Professor Jiang and go.

644
00:28:21,720 --> 00:28:23,180
That's about it for today.

645
00:28:23,270 --> 00:28:25,070
We'll get together another day.

646
00:28:25,710 --> 00:28:26,590
Bin has had too much to drink.

647
00:28:26,590 --> 00:28:27,700
I'm not drunk!

648
00:28:29,110 --> 00:28:29,910
Zhou Jin,

649
00:28:30,580 --> 00:28:33,130
what kind of nonsense marriage is this?

650
00:28:33,160 --> 00:28:34,750
Just to put your parents' minds at ease,

651
00:28:34,750 --> 00:28:36,460
you married him so casually!

652
00:28:36,500 --> 00:28:37,830
Do you even know him?

653
00:28:38,510 --> 00:28:39,810
Stop pointing your finger at him!

654
00:28:39,810 --> 00:28:41,250
Are you out of your mind, Yan Bin?

655
00:28:41,250 --> 00:28:42,290
Do you know him?

656
00:28:42,350 --> 00:28:44,270
Who are you to talk about him like that?

657
00:28:44,270 --> 00:28:46,170
Listen up, I've been
holding it in for a long time!

658
00:28:46,170 --> 00:28:47,720
You invited us to dinner,

659
00:28:47,740 --> 00:28:48,780
and I brought him.

660
00:28:48,830 --> 00:28:49,830
Did we eat?

661
00:28:49,830 --> 00:28:50,790
Did we drink?

662
00:28:50,820 --> 00:28:52,220
So what are you doing now?

663
00:28:53,160 --> 00:28:54,960
I treat you as a friend, and you?

664
00:28:55,490 --> 00:28:57,400
You've been
making things difficult for him.

665
00:28:57,400 --> 00:29:00,330
You've been
making things difficult for my husband!

666
00:29:00,460 --> 00:29:01,480
Making things difficult for him?

667
00:29:01,480 --> 00:29:02,880
I did it for your own good.

668
00:29:03,640 --> 00:29:04,240
If you really care about me,

669
00:29:04,240 --> 00:29:05,390
you shouldn't behave like this!

670
00:29:05,390 --> 00:29:06,710
First, don't humiliate him!

671
00:29:06,710 --> 00:29:07,470
Second,

672
00:29:07,830 --> 00:29:09,000
please sincerely

673
00:29:09,450 --> 00:29:10,710
give us your blessing.

674
00:29:11,070 --> 00:29:12,620
Give you my blessing?

675
00:29:12,810 --> 00:29:13,950
Give you my blessing?

676
00:29:13,950 --> 00:29:14,820
Let me tell you...

677
00:29:14,820 --> 00:29:16,680
Give you... Give you my blessing?

678
00:29:19,750 --> 00:29:20,640
From now on,

679
00:29:20,720 --> 00:29:21,850
we're good friends.

680
00:29:22,070 --> 00:29:23,670
No one can bully you anymore.

681
00:29:30,850 --> 00:29:35,510
[1997]

682
00:29:38,030 --> 00:29:40,240
She hit you. Why didn't you run?

683
00:29:43,680 --> 00:29:44,720
My dad said that

684
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:46,270
when someone shows concern for you,

685
00:29:46,270 --> 00:29:47,160
not answering them

686
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:48,030
is impolite.

687
00:29:48,740 --> 00:29:49,540
She...

688
00:29:50,960 --> 00:29:51,920
is pitiful.

689
00:29:52,920 --> 00:29:54,240
Just like my mom.

690
00:29:54,590 --> 00:29:56,640
You're the pitiful one when she hits you.

691
00:29:56,640 --> 00:29:58,040
You should tell your dad!

692
00:30:00,310 --> 00:30:02,310
Then there'd be no one at home again.

693
00:30:04,750 --> 00:30:06,210
Would you be alone at home?

694
00:30:07,200 --> 00:30:08,660
Are you afraid of the dark?

695
00:30:10,840 --> 00:30:12,170
You can stay at my place.

696
00:30:12,590 --> 00:30:14,050
My dad is a police officer.

697
00:30:14,050 --> 00:30:15,440
He's not afraid of any bad guys.

698
00:30:15,440 --> 00:30:16,500
He can protect you.

699
00:30:17,920 --> 00:30:18,450
Let's go.

700
00:30:21,160 --> 00:30:22,000
I...

701
00:30:22,420 --> 00:30:23,140
No need.

702
00:30:27,830 --> 00:30:28,750
I'm Zhou Jin.

703
00:30:29,440 --> 00:30:30,310
And you?

704
00:30:32,310 --> 00:30:33,240
Jiang Hansheng.

705
00:30:33,590 --> 00:30:34,400
From now on,

706
00:30:34,550 --> 00:30:35,720
we're good friends.

707
00:30:36,480 --> 00:30:37,480
Remember my name.

708
00:30:37,960 --> 00:30:39,560
No one can bully you anymore.

709
00:30:40,960 --> 00:30:42,030
Jiang Hansheng,

710
00:30:42,270 --> 00:30:43,200
trust me.

711
00:30:43,750 --> 00:30:44,280
Let's go!

712
00:30:44,480 --> 00:30:45,540
I'll take you home!

713
00:31:06,460 --> 00:31:07,190
Zhou Jin.

714
00:31:10,290 --> 00:31:11,030
What's wrong?

715
00:31:11,030 --> 00:31:12,830
You can't drive after drinking.

716
00:31:13,130 --> 00:31:14,210
You drank all the alcohol.

717
00:31:14,210 --> 00:31:15,070
I didn't drink.

718
00:31:24,750 --> 00:31:25,950
Are you feeling sick?

719
00:31:39,230 --> 00:31:40,490
Hansheng, we're home.

720
00:31:50,990 --> 00:31:52,590
Hansheng, get out of the car.

721
00:31:57,720 --> 00:31:58,440
Come on.

722
00:32:05,790 --> 00:32:06,590
What's wrong?

723
00:32:06,590 --> 00:32:07,990
Are you not feeling well?

724
00:32:43,440 --> 00:32:44,680
Are you feeling sick?

725
00:32:44,680 --> 00:32:45,610
Is it really bad?

726
00:32:46,240 --> 00:32:47,840
Do you feel like throwing up?

727
00:32:54,920 --> 00:32:55,550
I don't know

728
00:32:55,550 --> 00:32:57,210
what Yan Bin told you tonight.

729
00:32:58,630 --> 00:33:00,090
But that's all in the past.

730
00:33:02,000 --> 00:33:03,930
Do you still have feelings for him?

731
00:33:04,200 --> 00:33:05,270
I don't.

732
00:33:07,310 --> 00:33:09,110
Then do you have feelings for me?

733
00:33:15,920 --> 00:33:17,650
You don't have feelings for me.

734
00:33:18,700 --> 00:33:19,630
You're drunk.

735
00:33:22,600 --> 00:33:23,280
Zhou Jin,

736
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:26,030
you can't lie.

737
00:33:28,030 --> 00:33:30,160
Can we wait until you sober up tomorrow

738
00:33:30,790 --> 00:33:32,050
and discuss this then?

739
00:33:42,590 --> 00:33:44,200
You still don't have feelings for me.

740
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:45,790
That's not true.

741
00:34:09,630 --> 00:34:10,590
Are you mad?

742
00:34:17,280 --> 00:34:18,210
Jiang Hansheng.

743
00:34:20,449 --> 00:34:21,980
I like having you by my side.

744
00:34:30,440 --> 00:34:31,370
Jiang Hansheng,

745
00:34:31,560 --> 00:34:32,360
let's go home.

746
00:34:39,850 --> 00:34:43,469
♪ I should never have let you bear this ♪

747
00:34:45,400 --> 00:34:47,000
Do you really want to know me?

748
00:34:47,139 --> 00:34:51,230
♪ I always want to give you
everything I have ♪

749
00:34:49,880 --> 00:34:51,190
What if Yan Bin is right

750
00:34:52,469 --> 00:34:54,469
and I'm not the person you think I am?

751
00:34:54,520 --> 00:34:58,470
♪ If only it could win your heart,
even for a moment ♪

752
00:34:56,030 --> 00:34:57,030
What do you mean?

753
00:34:58,890 --> 00:35:02,220
♪ Look at the fish
swimming in the ocean depths ♪

754
00:35:03,760 --> 00:35:06,040
♪ They're so free ♪

755
00:35:06,550 --> 00:35:07,480
Jiang Hansheng!

756
00:35:07,630 --> 00:35:08,190
Zhou Jin.

757
00:35:09,410 --> 00:35:13,540
♪ I never want to see you hang your head ♪

758
00:35:10,400 --> 00:35:11,400
Will you hate me?

759
00:35:13,190 --> 00:35:15,250
Don't be dramatic when you're drunk.

760
00:35:16,710 --> 00:35:17,370
Zhou Jin...

761
00:35:17,420 --> 00:35:20,490
♪ I keep dreaming of
what lies ahead for us ♪

762
00:35:19,840 --> 00:35:20,670
I love you.

763
00:35:24,050 --> 00:35:27,990
♪ If only it could keep us
in love forever ♪

764
00:35:28,510 --> 00:35:31,740
♪ Look at the zebras ♪

765
00:35:49,310 --> 00:35:53,610
[1997]

766
00:35:54,190 --> 00:35:55,120
Jiang Hansheng!

767
00:35:55,190 --> 00:35:55,800
Mentor!

768
00:35:56,000 --> 00:35:56,600
Hansheng.

769
00:35:56,630 --> 00:35:57,070
Jiang Hansheng.

770
00:35:57,070 --> 00:35:57,510
Mentor,

771
00:35:57,510 --> 00:35:58,480
we've searched everywhere on this side!

772
00:35:58,480 --> 00:35:59,590
We can't find the kid.

773
00:35:59,590 --> 00:36:00,960
Then look further away!

774
00:36:01,230 --> 00:36:01,800
Hurry, let's go!

775
00:36:01,800 --> 00:36:03,000
Go search over there!

776
00:36:03,190 --> 00:36:04,190
Jiang Hansheng!

777
00:36:04,190 --> 00:36:05,360
Hansheng!

778
00:36:05,480 --> 00:36:06,800
Jiang Hansheng!

779
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:08,000
Hansheng!

780
00:36:08,110 --> 00:36:09,110
Hansheng!

781
00:36:09,150 --> 00:36:11,070
Jiang Hansheng!

782
00:36:22,320 --> 00:36:23,440
We've searched everywhere.

783
00:36:23,440 --> 00:36:24,110
Mentor!

784
00:36:24,150 --> 00:36:26,280
Liu, how's the situation on your side?

785
00:36:26,320 --> 00:36:28,280
We've searched everywhere
but didn't find him, Mentor.

786
00:36:28,280 --> 00:36:29,280
Zhou,

787
00:36:29,460 --> 00:36:30,760
we've searched all around here.

788
00:36:30,760 --> 00:36:32,420
Should we search further out?

789
00:36:34,710 --> 00:36:36,190
Has the station sent anyone?

790
00:36:36,190 --> 00:36:37,320
Let them search this area

791
00:36:37,320 --> 00:36:38,510
carefully again!

792
00:36:38,920 --> 00:36:39,550
Mentor,

793
00:36:39,590 --> 00:36:41,720
w-we've already searched carefully.

794
00:36:42,250 --> 00:36:42,730
Well,

795
00:36:42,810 --> 00:36:45,220
where could a little boy like him
possibly go?

796
00:36:45,220 --> 00:36:47,320
Why hasn't the boy's father come back yet?

797
00:36:47,320 --> 00:36:48,720
He said he's almost here!

798
00:36:48,960 --> 00:36:49,760
Let's do this—

799
00:36:50,120 --> 00:36:52,930
let's go check... um... his place again!

800
00:36:52,960 --> 00:36:54,400
Maybe he went back, right?

801
00:36:54,400 --> 00:36:55,190
Okay, let's go.

802
00:36:55,190 --> 00:36:56,790
-Come on, let's go.
-Come on.

803
00:37:13,960 --> 00:37:14,890
Jiang Hansheng.

804
00:37:23,510 --> 00:37:24,510
Jiang Hansheng.

805
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:30,150
Are you alright?

806
00:37:33,270 --> 00:37:34,960
I miss my mom.

807
00:37:37,440 --> 00:37:39,150
Then why are you hiding here?

808
00:37:40,840 --> 00:37:41,840
My mom...

809
00:37:43,550 --> 00:37:45,510
is lying in a dark place.

810
00:38:15,920 --> 00:38:16,760
Hansheng.

811
00:38:21,510 --> 00:38:23,230
I think I remember something.

812
00:38:44,970 --> 00:38:46,630
You found something already?

813
00:38:47,730 --> 00:38:48,330
Jin.

814
00:38:49,400 --> 00:38:50,480
I'll just tell you,

815
00:38:50,480 --> 00:38:51,580
and you take it as is.

816
00:38:51,580 --> 00:38:52,440
Can you do that?

817
00:38:52,530 --> 00:38:53,460
I'll try my best.

818
00:38:53,800 --> 00:38:55,340
Back during the follow-up manhunt
after the 8/17 Case,

819
00:38:55,340 --> 00:38:56,640
Yao Weihai was the first

820
00:38:56,640 --> 00:38:59,370
to find the hiding place
of some of the criminals.

821
00:39:00,110 --> 00:39:01,490
He made a great contribution—

822
00:39:01,490 --> 00:39:02,930
that was beyond dispute,

823
00:39:02,970 --> 00:39:05,010
and was widely known.

824
00:39:05,820 --> 00:39:08,080
But that's also when the leads went cold.

825
00:39:08,460 --> 00:39:09,810
Don't you suspect that the reason he

826
00:39:09,810 --> 00:39:11,330
found the criminals first

827
00:39:11,510 --> 00:39:14,310
was because someone on the inside
was helping him?

828
00:39:14,370 --> 00:39:15,700
It's not what you think.

829
00:39:16,810 --> 00:39:18,140
There was an informant.

830
00:39:18,490 --> 00:39:19,300
The informant

831
00:39:19,330 --> 00:39:22,060
provided him with
very important intelligence.

832
00:39:22,340 --> 00:39:23,600
Who was the informant?

833
00:39:24,010 --> 00:39:25,200
I wasn't able to find him.

834
00:39:25,200 --> 00:39:26,850
Since informants have to be protected,

835
00:39:26,850 --> 00:39:29,080
records about the person
might have been made confidential

836
00:39:29,080 --> 00:39:30,330
or destroyed.

837
00:39:30,730 --> 00:39:31,860
At least at my level,

838
00:39:31,880 --> 00:39:33,080
I can't find out more.

839
00:39:33,440 --> 00:39:35,230
And it's not appropriate to dig deeper.

840
00:39:35,230 --> 00:39:37,860
After all, Yao Weihai is leading
the task force.

841
00:39:37,860 --> 00:39:39,520
That could create conflicts.

842
00:39:42,390 --> 00:39:44,260
That informant had direct contact

843
00:39:44,260 --> 00:39:45,590
with the criminal gang.

844
00:39:47,130 --> 00:39:48,290
Can I meet him?

845
00:39:52,900 --> 00:39:54,420
That would be very difficult.

846
00:39:54,420 --> 00:39:55,590
Can you help me,

847
00:39:55,620 --> 00:39:56,260
Wei?

848
00:39:57,960 --> 00:39:58,850
Jin,

849
00:39:59,280 --> 00:40:01,120
I can only do my best.

850
00:40:01,680 --> 00:40:02,590
As long as it doesn't

851
00:40:02,590 --> 00:40:04,720
cause any danger or create any threat,

852
00:40:05,180 --> 00:40:06,310
I'll try to help you.

853
00:40:06,330 --> 00:40:08,060
But you still have to remember,

854
00:40:08,130 --> 00:40:09,330
the greater the hope,

855
00:40:09,620 --> 00:40:11,480
the greater the disappointment.

856
00:40:13,440 --> 00:40:14,400
I know.

857
00:40:15,630 --> 00:40:17,430
I'm used to being disappointed.

858
00:40:20,080 --> 00:40:20,640
Okay.

859
00:40:21,770 --> 00:40:22,830
Wait for my update.

860
00:41:08,010 --> 00:41:11,200
♪ Just one more second ♪

861
00:41:10,270 --> 00:41:11,070
You're awake.

862
00:41:11,870 --> 00:41:15,170
♪ When you're feeling low, is there ♪

863
00:41:15,320 --> 00:41:17,440
♪ Someone to hold you? ♪

864
00:41:18,050 --> 00:41:21,370
♪ When you're trapped, don't you ♪

865
00:41:21,410 --> 00:41:23,340
♪ Wan to escape? ♪

866
00:41:24,220 --> 00:41:27,920
♪ I know how strong you are ♪

867
00:41:27,030 --> 00:41:28,890
Do you still remember last night?

868
00:41:31,280 --> 00:41:32,210
Sorry, Zhou Jin.

869
00:41:32,880 --> 00:41:36,070
♪ Just one more second ♪

870
00:41:33,590 --> 00:41:34,360
I think...

871
00:41:34,840 --> 00:41:35,770
I drank too much.

872
00:41:36,700 --> 00:41:39,950
♪ Did you throw away ♪

873
00:41:40,330 --> 00:41:42,380
♪ The expired drinks? ♪

874
00:41:42,900 --> 00:41:46,450
♪ Though it's lost, you keep ♪

875
00:41:46,740 --> 00:41:48,740
♪ Looking for it ♪

876
00:41:48,890 --> 00:41:50,060
Your ears are red.

877
00:41:49,770 --> 00:41:53,400
♪ I know how fragile you are ♪

878
00:42:03,370 --> 00:42:04,250
Let's go back.

879
00:42:13,990 --> 00:42:17,380
[Zhizi Alley]

880
00:42:19,920 --> 00:42:22,580
You still haven't been
to see my brother, right?

881
00:42:26,320 --> 00:42:27,520
The day after tomorrow,

882
00:42:27,520 --> 00:42:28,920
come with me to visit him.

883
00:42:29,750 --> 00:42:30,420
Okay.

884
00:42:36,280 --> 00:42:38,280
Feels like it's going to rain again.

885
00:42:55,990 --> 00:42:56,790
What's wrong?

886
00:42:59,510 --> 00:43:00,110
Nothing.
